Members of the House of Representatives have donated their two months’ salary amounting to N226.9m to support government effort to curtail the spread of COVID-19. The House decision was announced by Speaker Femi Gbajabiamila in a video message to Nigerians yesterday. “We have in the House of Representatives jointly committed to contributing 100% of our salaries for the next two months to the fight against COVID-19 in Nigeria,” he said. Our correspondent reports that at the moment, there are 358 lawmakers at the green chamber as two of the members have died. A serving lawmaker, who spoke to our correspondent said the last salary he received was N317,000. Two months salaries of the 358 lawmakers will be N226,972,000. COVID-19: Senators, Reps under pressure to donate March salary Reps give 2-month salaries to fight Covid-19 Senators, Reps get N93m as recess allowance